body:
Run rclone about remote:

If the space isn't reporting, that would be it.

root@Unraid-Server:~# rclone about XXX:
Total:   28 TiB
Used:    27.996 TiB
Free:    3.720 GiB
and the file is too big for that I'd imagine.

yeah :) 

but anyway, if upload fails with insufficient space, it should just stop, it does the same on google drive without problem (hard failing...)

i just tried the latest beta 1.6.5 same thing:
2023/09/23 22:06:20 ERROR : Dropbox root 'XXX/is7npm4pf8tr0c9otsuca7omdo': sync batch commit: failed to commit batch length 1: batch had 1 errors: last error: path/insufficient_space

2023/09/23 22:06:20 ERROR : XXX/XXX: Not deleting source as copy failed: upload failed: batch upload failed: path/insufficient_space

... but keeps doing

can you open it again? Maybe its just not well handled on batch upload?
That beta was never tested/merged from the thread so I guess an enhancement perhaps.
ah, so if it gets merged then it would be an easy fix?

rename.to: Dropbox: insufficient_space not a fatal error

body:
This change did get merged in 4b9da601be9422382aaa41c08d6b7eb601c95658

What it does is stop that file being retried. It doesn't stop the next file being retried though!

We could upgrade that error to a Fatal error which will stop the sync immediately.

I guess since we have a very clear signal from dropbox that the disk is full we should do that.

What do you think @animosity22 and @eihns ?

ofc. Why keep working when there is no (or very little) space...?

How can i test it?

Please give this a test

[v1.65.0-beta.7390.10490bfd0.fix-7334-dropbox-full](https://beta.rclone.org/branch/fix-7334-dropbox-full/v1.65.0-beta.7390.10490bfd0.fix-7334-dropbox-full/) on branch [fix-7334-dropbox-full](https://github.com/rclone/rclone/tree/fix-7334-dropbox-full) (uploaded in 15-30 mins)
